        "timestamp": "2019-11-11 17:52:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\nBrian FYI - today on the PTL Call the issue came up that JDK 11 may not have an Alpine image available. It was noted that JDK 12 and 13 do, some projects are just going to push to that version. But they could use the source/target variables for compilation to a specific JDK version. Thus, you may want to consider perhaps doing this for JDK 13?? Let's discuss this.\n\nMaybe as a good start, get oparent upgraded to 11. Probably moving to 13 wouldn't be as hard.\n\nI have a resource becoming available soon who can help.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
